1. Create an array of 5 by 5. Find the maximum and before the maximal elements of each line.
2. Create an arbitrary size array. Fill in with random numbers. Find the number of rows, where all numbers are ascending
3. Create an arbitrary size array. Fill in with random numbers. Find all columns, where all elements go down the decay.
4. Create an arbitrary size array. Fill in random numbers. Change the maximum and minimum elements in each column.
5. Create an arbitrary size array. Fill with random numbers. Swap the left and right sides of the matrix
